Canon has unveiled the mirrorless EOS M50 interchangeable-lens camera, which offers 4K video recording. The EOS M50 sports a 24.1MP APS-C CMOS sensor, which promises less noise and high definition in low-light situations. “Our core goal when developing new entry-level interchangeable-lens cameras is to meld high-quality features and usability together,” said Canon. Additional features of the EOS M50 include: